Package entities

Class Order

java.lang.Object
entities.Order
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Order extends Object implements Serializable
This class represents an order in the system. It includes details about the items in the order, the supplier, the customer, and various order attributes.

      public Order(List<ItemInOrder> itemsList, int orderID, String recipient, String recipientPhone, SupplyMethod supplyOption, Supplier supplier, Customer customer, Branch branchName, String requestedDate, String requestedTime, OrderType type, float totalPrice, String approvalTimer, String arrivalTime, String status)
      Constructs an Order with specified details.
      Parameters:
      itemsList - A list of ItemInOrder objects representing the items in the order.
      orderID - The unique identifier for the order.
      recipient - The name of the recipient of the order.
      recipientPhone - The phone number of the recipient.
      supplyOption - The supply method for the order, represented by an instance of SupplyMethod.
      supplier - The Supplier who provides the items in the order.
      customer - The Customer who placed the order.
      branchName - The Branch where the order is placed.
      requestedDate - The date when the order is requested
      requestedTime - The time when the order is requested
      type - The type of the order, represented by an instance of OrderType.
      totalPrice - The total price of the order.
      approvalTimer - The time order is approved
      arrivalTime - The arrival time of the order.
      status - The current status of the order.
